On the South Shore train bound for Chicago one Saturday afternoon, me and 4 friends/relatives were on one car that had a number of people on it.  One guy was listening to his walkman and was singing out loud and it contained a few choice words.  An elderly couple sitting behind him was getting agitated on what he was saying and made them unconfortable.  Now myself and my friends could here him as well and it didn't bother us so we chose to ignore him best we could and carry on out conversation.  Well, the older gentleman tapped him on his shoulder and asked him if he could refrain from singing out loud with words that were unappropriate to be saying in public.  The man with the walkman told the old guy to shut the hell up and continued his singing.  The older gentleman asked the conductor/ticket agent to ask the man to stop his obscene singing to which she obliged.  The man with the walkman told her to leave him alone and told the old man to mind his fucking business and to stop fucking with him.  he said it rather loud in his face.  Well, the train conductor called ahead and had the Hammond police meet us at the 2nd Hammond stop and the cops arrested the man and charge him with aggrevated assault.<br>
<br>
Hmmm, now tell me how swearing in public isn't bad and doesn't cause problems?  I of course found this all amusing when it was happening much like everyone on this board finds this amusing that this happened but rather than morally saying that public swearing is bad, you are rather putting Lynliss down for doing something that is against the rules with a filter or not.  If Lynliss has a personal vendeta with Seethur, that is for the 2 of them to work out or if it's with CiH, it's for the respected parties to work out, but DO NOT defend public swearing in a game that explicitly says no foul language.<br>
